    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="275"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Goodnow</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 5, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Conger-Squiers messages Ragsdale, dated July 21, reads as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>All well; no fighting since 16th by agreement; enough provisions; little
                            ammunition; hope speedy relief.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Sheng to-day communicated Imperial edict July 30, ordering Yung Lu provide escort
                    ministers Tientsin when ministers fix date. Edict says ministers can receive
                    messages not in cipher. Yet plain messages were returned to consuls
                    yesterday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Goodnow.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
